    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10675804>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Illustrations of female epigynum of Tullgrenella, dorsal view. A–E morenensis group: A T. morenensis (Tullgren, 1905) (MCN 19940), B T. guayapae Galiano, 1970 (MCN 55520), C T. brescoviti Estol, Marta & Rodrigues, 2020 (MCN 24104), D T. musica (Mello-Leitão,1945) (MCN 53372), E T. corrugata Galiano, 1981 (MACN-Ar 7206). F–H quadripunctata group: F T. quadripunctata (Mello-Leitão, 1944) (MCTP 2239), G T. nadjae Estol, Marta & Rodrigues, 2020 (MCN 56814), H T. lunata (Mello-Leitão, 1944) (MACN-Ar 6214). I–J melanica group: I T. melanica (Mello-Leitão, 1941) (MACN-Ar 6244), J T. yungae Galiano, 1970 (MCTP 39713). K–O serrana group: K T. serrana Galiano, 1970 (MCTP 12173), L T. legalissima Marta & Hagopián, sp. nov. (IBSP 118228), M T. aisenbergae Marta, sp. nov. (IBSP 123129), N T. gertschi Galiano, 1981 (MACN-Ar 7206), O T. sciosciae Marta & Bustamante, sp. nov. (MCTP 31135). P–Q peniaflorensis group: P T. peniaflorensis Galiano, 1970 (MACN-Ar 6242), Q T. selenita Galiano, 1970 (FNAC 36). Scale bars: 0.25 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10675804/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10675806>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Male of T. morenensis (Tullgren, 1905) (MACN-Ar 42165). A habitus, dorsal view, red arrow: spotted coloration pattern. B same, ventral view. C left palp, ventral view, red arrow: tegulum central depression, purple arrow: tegular membranous process. D same, retrolateral view, red arrow: hook between RTA and prolatero-dorsal tibial apophysis, red dashed line:prolaterodorsal tibial apophysis. Scale bars: A–B 2 mm, C–D 0.50 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10675806/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10675812>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Male of T. guayapae Galiano, 1970.A habitus (MCN 21128), dorsal view. B same, ventral view. C left palp (MCN 55543), ventral view, red arrow: tegulum central depression, purple arrow: tegular membranous process. D same, retrolateral view, red arrow: hook between RTA and prolatero-dorsal tibial apophysis, red dashed line: prolatero-dorsal tibial apophysis. Scale bars: A–B 2 mm, C–D 0.50 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10675812/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10675814>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Female of T. guayapae Galiano, 1970. A habitus (MCN 21128), dorsal view, red arrow: spotted coloration pattern. B same, ventral view. C epigynum (MCN 55520), ventral view, red arrow: subseptum. D same, dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B 2 mm, C–D 0.25 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10675814/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10675838>
    dc:description "FIGURE 18. Scanning electronic microscopy of spinnerets of female T. guayapae Galiano, 1970 (MCN 55520). A general. B left ALS. C PLSs. D left PLS, zoom." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10675838/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10675840>
    dc:description "FIGURE 19. Scanning electronic microscopy of first leg of male T. guayapae Galiano, 1970. A general, with bristles and tarsal organ. B distal location of tarsal organ. C–D zoom of tarsal organ." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10675840/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10675880>
    dc:description "FIGURE 31. Scanning electronic microscopy of epiandrous spigots. A–B T. yungae Galiano, 1970 (MCTP 36001): A fusules, B zoom of fusules and bristles. C–D T. guayapae Galiano, 1970 (MCTP 40517): C fusules, D zoom of fusules and bristles." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10675880/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10675928>
    dc:description "FIGURE 50. Neotropical and Andean regionalization (Morrone 2014) and distributional records for species of the morenensis group. A Neotropical, South America, Brazilian subregion Chacoan subregion, South America Transition Zone and Andean region. B Southern South America, focusing on species occurrence. C habitat inference, Argentina: La Pampa, Lihuel Calel, photographed by collector Ivan Magalhães." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10675928/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

